, and famines. Robert Frank describes how the strongest predictor of our willingness to support climate-friendly policies, install solar panels, or buy an electric car is the number of people we know who have already done so. In the face of stakes that could not be higher, the book explains how we could redirect trillions of dollars annually in support of carbon-free energy sources, all without requiring painful sacrifices from anyone.Most of us would agree that we need to take responsibility for our own choices, but with more supportive social environments, each of us is more likely to make choices that benefit everyone. Under the Influence shows how.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aSocial influence. 0aSocial planning. 0aSocial pressure. 0aVices. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Economics / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Business and Economics 2020 Englishz978311070479208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Economics 2020z9783110704624oZDB-23-DBV08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPrinceton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020z978311069008840uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780691198828zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780691198828423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780691198828.jpg  a978-3-11-069008-8  Princeton University Press Complete eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070479-2  EBOOK PACKAGE Business and Economics 2020 Englishb2020  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEB